/* ============================================================================
   58. Conclusion and Best Practices for Scalability
============================================================================ */

/*
   - Use CSS Grid for complex layouts and Flexbox for simpler, one-dimensional layouts.
   - Leverage CSS Variables for maintainable and customizable themes across the application.
   - Avoid excessive specificity; keep selectors simple and use classes as much as possible.
   - Always test accessibility features such as contrast, focus states, and screen reader support.
   - Use animation sparingly to enhance user experience without overwhelming the interface.
   - Always perform performance optimization for faster loading times.
*/

/* ============================================================================
   59. Advanced Interactive Components
============================================================================ */

/* Tooltip */
.tooltip {
    position: absolute;
    background-color: #333;
    color: #fff;
    padding: 8px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    opacity: 0;
    visibility: hidden;
    transition: opacity 0.3s ease-in-out;
}

